<ul><li>The acceleration is&nbsp;<b>greatest</b>&nbsp;when the gradient of the velocity-time graph is the greatest when the&nbsp;<b>velocity is zero</b>&nbsp;and occurs at&nbsp;<b>maximum displacement</b>&nbsp;in either direction.</li><li>The acceleration is&nbsp;<b>zero</b>&nbsp;when the gradient of the velocity-time graph is zero when the&nbsp;<b>displacement is zero</b>&nbsp;and the&nbsp;<b>velocity is a maximum</b>.</li></ul>